The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, July 19, 2004 				 Nirvana in porcelain
																								A kaleidoscopic view is what our world offers to its citizens. The diversity in the cultures that spans the length and breadth of the universe is a good enough reason for amazement. And the wealth that is born out of these different cultural melting pots is an art connoisseurs delight. The very mention of Chinese porcelain conjures up in the mind an association of daintiness that has come to become synonymous with porcelain. Nirvana China House is the new address in the city where those with an appreciation of the delicate can drop in for a look at the original Chinese porcelain from Jingdezhen in South China. Calcuttans, specially those with an eye for the arts, ought to feel lucky because Jingdezhen prides itself on being the Porcelain Capital of the World. By courtesy of Nirvana China House, the city will now get a glimpse into the pristine world of porcelain; on display at the exhibition are original Chinese artifacts ranging from vases, paintings, statuettes, lanterns to furniture and other objects d art.																								Event: An exhibition of original Chinese porcelain																								When: Till July 25; 11 am - 8 pm																								Where: Nirvana China House, 8B, Middleton Street
